7.1. Payment
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The balance on the card account falls due for payment and the payment is
withdrawn on the due date from the current account you have chosen.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
The agreed credit limit is the maximum sum you can withdraw from your
card account. If, at any time, the balance exceeds the agreed credit
limit, &BANKNAVN. will be entitled to request immediate payment on
request of any sums in excess of the limit. &BANKNAVN. may choose to
claim material breach of contract - see Articles 2.16 and 2.17 - with
the effect, inter alia, of the full balance on the card account falling
due for payment.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
7.2. Interest and overdraft rates
:SKRSLUT.
.br
Interest is calculated from the invoicing date (i.e. at the end of the
collection period) as a monthly rate on the opening balance for the
period, less timely credits (your deposits etc.) during the collection
period.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
If you receive an invoice and pay the full balance on your card account
on time, no interest will be charged on the subsequent invoice. This
means that you will only be charged interest if you choose to pay only
part of the balance and carry the remaining balance over for subsequent
payment.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
Interest is calculated at the rate applied by &BANKNAVN. at any
time, see the price list. The interest rate is variable and may be
altered in accordance with &BANKNAVN.'s general terms and conditions
of business. As regards interest on overdrafts, the regulation
stated in Article 3.5 will apply.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
7.3 Duration of the agreement
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The credit agreement/credit limit are valid until further notice. For
terms and conditions concerning termination of the agreement, see
Article 2.16.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
